Sorcerous Origins.Divine Soul:
{{Main|Divine soul}}
Some sorcerers were blessed with divine souls that granted them access to [[divine magic]] rather than the arcane. This favor from the heavens was sometimes the result of [[angel]]ic lineage or a momentous birth associated with a holy prophecy. Within some lands, divine souls were elevated to near-deific statuses themselves, while in others they were perceived as threats to established clergies.

Divine soul sorcerers drew upon certain divine spells, which differed according to their [[alignment|ethical and moral outlook of the world]]. They were each granted blessings from on high, and were bolstered with powerful restorative energy. Over time their physical form took on the appearance of [[celestial]]s, as otherworldly wings would extended from their back at times.

Sorcerous Origins.Dragon Magic:
{{Main|Draconic bloodline}}
[[File:Dragonbornsorcerer.jpg|thumb|left|200px|A [[white dragon|white]] [[dragonborn]] draconic sorcerer.]]
One archetypical source of sorcery was the power inherent to dragons. Sorcerers that drew upon this wellspring were granted magical power by some innate connection to dragons, either through draconic bloodline, blood ties or magical infusion, such as being bathed in dragonblood as an infant. Dragon magic sorcerers were emotionally and quite often physically powerful beings.{{cite book/Player's Handbook 2|151}} 

Dragon magic sorcerers were awe-inspiring and mighty, capable of channeling their pain into powerful rage and using their physical strength to bolster the power of their spells. They were exceptionally resilient and difficult to kill. Dragon magic sorcerers were blessed with both an affinity for and resilience to one of the elemental energies used by most dragons in their breath weapons, such as acid, cold or fire.{{cite book/Player's Handbook 2|136-137}} Those sorcerers of draconic bloodline that expertly honed their abilities could draw upon the frightening presence of their forebears and even grow a pair of wings, granting them the ability of flight.

Sorcerous Origins.Storm Magic:
{{Main|Storm sorcery}}
Some sorcerers of the Realms gained their abilities from the primordial powers of existence, such as the element of [[air]] itself. While others avoid gale winds and lightning blasts for their safety, storm sorcerers felt perfectly at home within, drawn to the fury and unrelenting power. In fact these powerful spellcasters may even have originally gained their power from a terrible storm that impacted their life (such as the [[Great Rain]]), either by being born within one or nearly dying from the destruction and havoc one caused.<ref name=XGtE-p50-51" /> Many of these individuals chose to live at sea, utilizing their powers to help navigate ships and keep aquatic dangers at bay.

Storm sorcerers gained an innate understanding of the [[primordial language]] of the cosmos, along with its four dialects including [[auran]]. They quickly learned how to summon gusts of wind, and in time gained limited control over weather itself. Over time their bodies became resistant and even immune to the effects of lightning and thunder, and in some instances could conduct and channel bolts of lightning within at will. These sorcerers whose souls had been entirely in tune with the winds even gained the ability of flight, and could even lift others alongside them as if by the gale forces of an unrelenting storm.

